{"key":"post-13248726","value":"<?xml version=\"1.0\"?>\n<post>\n<id>13248726</id>\n<content>I've never yet seen a pin form in the crater from a 'twist and pulled' mushroom.&amp;nbsp; However, I have seen green molds infect the wound that is left from ripping a mushroom out, rather than cutting it at the base.&amp;nbsp; This is the reason I suggest cutting mushrooms at harvest rather than the old advice of 'twist and pull'.&lt;br /&gt;&lt;br /&gt;Obviously new pins won't form on the stumps, but rather in between them.&lt;br /&gt;RR</content>\n<name>RogerRabbit</name>\n<next></next>\n<prev>13247715</prev>\n<first>13237038</first>\n<last>13248726</last>\n<when>1285519561</when>\n<utime>09/26/10 07:46 PM</utime>\n</post>"}